Subject: [PATCH] e1000e: clear PHY wakeup bit after LCD reset on 82577/82578

[ commit 7d3cabbcc86f7f69c47cb20c23ee84350ae6cfbb upstream ]

Performing a dummy read of the PHY Wakeup Control (WUC) register clears the
wakeup enable bit set by an PHY reset.  If this bit remains set, link
problems may occur.

Signed-off-by: Bruce Allan <bruce.w.allan@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: xianchao Zhang <xianchao.zhang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/e1000e/ich8lan.c |    8 ++++++++
 1 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/e1000e/ich8lan.c b/drivers/net/e1000e/ich8lan.c
index db55c34..e6008a0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/e1000e/ich8lan.c
+++ b/drivers/net/e1000e/ich8lan.c
@@ -780,6 +780,10 @@ static s32 e1000_phy_hw_reset_ich8lan(struct e1000_hw *hw)
 	if (ret_val)
 		return ret_val;
 
+	/* Dummy read to clear the phy wakeup bit after lcd reset */
+	if (hw->mac.type == e1000_pchlan)
+		e1e_rphy(hw, BM_WUC, &reg);
+
